Set the font used when rendering text.

### syntax

~~~ python
setFont(filename)
~~~

### parameters

filename | path to font file

### additional arguments

size | font size (default=10)

### examples

#### set font type


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "text-font", "set-font-type.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)

   textFont('data/fonts/DroidSans.ttf')
   text("Droid Sans", 0, 0, 5)

   textFont('data/fonts/times.ttf')
   text("Times", 0, 0, 0)

   textFont('data/fonts/webdings.ttf')
   text("Webdings", 0, 0, -5)
~~~


#### set font type and size


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "text-font", "set-font-type-and-size.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)

   textFont('data/fonts/DroidSans.ttf', 32)
   text("Droid Sans", 0, 0, 5)

   textFont('data/fonts/times.ttf', 32)
   text("Times", 0, 0, 0)

   textFont('data/fonts/webdings.ttf', 32)
   text("Webdings", 0, 0, -5)
~~~

